==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Swale
<hw>Swale</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Icel.
<ets>svalr</ets> cool, <ets>svala</ets> to cool.]</ety> <def>A valley or
low place; a tract of low, and usually wet, land; a moor; a fen.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng. & Local, U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swale</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Swale
<hw>Swale</hw>, <pos>v. i. & t.</pos> <def>To melt and waste away; to
singe. See <er>Sweal</er>, <pos>v.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swale</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Swale
<hw>Swale</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A gutter in a candle.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swallet</ent>⟦br⟧
